    "body": "@soltanmm-google: I don't think I yet know enough to say.\n\n@dgquintas: tell us more about \"[otherwise](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/79620aaa1052fd02539a36caa63cbe24a2087b0f/include/grpc/impl/codegen/byte_buffer.h#L97)\"? Does zero indicate a programming defect or an operational failure? Is it safe to reattempt the call to `grpc_byte_buffer_reader_init`? If we should raise an exception, what kind of guidance should we offer to Python applications about how to handle it? Should we just crash the process and exit right away with an attitude of \"gRPC is over; go home\"?\n"
