    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "It indicates an operational failure (eg, data corruption). It should be possible to retry, even though data may have been lost. Currently, \"otherwise\" only happens when decompression of a byte buffer fails (https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/src/core/lib/surface/byte_buffer_reader.c#L68). Basically we detect the corruption because compression and its checksums. On an uncompressed buffer, the corrupted data would simply be returned and no one would be the wiser.\n"
  },
